2008-10-05  Jost Boekemeier  <jostb@@intern>

	* server/php/java/script/CGIRunner.java
	(run): Do not call flush() in the finally block to work around a
	bug in the Sun "Grassfish" J2EE server, which assumes that the
	current thread is an instance of SSLWorkerThread, see
	SSLOutputWriter, line 28: (SSLWorkerThread)Thread.currentThread();
	=> java.lang.ClassCastException: php.java.script.HttpProxy cannot
	be cast to
	com.sun.enterprise.web.connector.grizzly.ssl.SSLWorkerThread
	
	
