1.195
log
@Release 5.3.3.1
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
2008-11-26  Jost Boekemeier  <jostb@@intern>
d3 3
a5 3
        * server/php/java/bridge/JavaBridge.java
        (typeExists): cast the result to boolean, so that java_autoload() can
        report a failure.
d28 6
a33 2
        * VERSION, php-java-bridge.spec: Version 5.3.3.1
        
d46 1
a46 12
	java(...). Unfortunately this write-write-read on protocol level
	will make the bridge 4 times slower on operating systems which use
	BSD's original TCP/IP stack w/o John Nagle's ack delay
	fix (introduced in 2006). The alternative would have been to make
	the bridge a little bit slower on *all* operating systems by using
	a write-read-write-read. But since all modern operating
	systems (except *BSD and Mac OSX) already contain the fix, we have
	decided against it. If your operating system uses the original BSD
	TCP/IP protocol stack, please either upgrade your operating system
	or switch off Nagle's algorithm for local TCP sockets. On BSD and
	Mac OSX you can also use Unix Domain Sockets to communicate with
	the back end, see the README "BSD and Mac OSX issues" for details.
@


