1.154
log
@Release-3-1-8devel
@
text
@a2 45
	* server/php/java/bridge/ContextRunner.java 
	(readLength): Read lenght >255 correctly. Thanks to Marco Walther.

	* java.c (java_cast, do_cast): New procedure for compatibility with the
	new pure PHP implementation.

	* PROTOCOL.TXT: describe header.

	* server/php/java/bridge/Base64EncodingOutputBuffer.java,
	server/php/java/bridge/ClassicResponse.java,
	server/php/java/bridge/HexOutputBuffer.java: New files to help the
	pure PHP implementation.

	* server/php/java/bridge/Request, server/php/java/bridge/Response:
	The pure PHP implementation doesn't know about context ID's.

	* server/php/java/bridge/JavaBridge.java
	(offsetExists,offsetGet,offsetUnset): The server must coerce to
	Number, not the client.

	* server/php/java/bridge/PhpMap.java
	(offsetExists,offsetGet,offsetUnset): Removed, now in
	JavaBridge.java.
	
	* server/php/java/bridge/Options.java: Rewritten to disable
	context ID's.

	* server/php/java/bridge/Snarf.java: Use the pure PHP
	implementation, if available.

	* server/php/java/bridge/Parser.java: Initialize the default
	options, according to PROTOCOL.TXT.
	
	* javabridge/Client.php, javabridge/GlobalRef.php,
	javabridge/IDocHandler.php, javabridge/Java.php,
	javabridge/JavaProxy.php, javabridge/Parser.php,
	javabridge/Protocol.php, javabridge/README: Removed.
	
	* java/Client.php, java/GlobalRef.php,
	java/IDocHandler.php, java/Java.php,
	java/JavaProxy.php, java/Parser.php,
	java/Protocol.php, java/README: New from the javabridge/* files.
	
2006-08-13  Jost Boekemeier  <jostb@@intern>

